shared_text:
Governor Doug Burgum
September 10 at 10:10 AM ¬∑

In 2019, suicide was the second leading cause of death for North Dakotans between the ages of 10-34. We've proclaimed September as Suicide Prevention Month to bring attention to this public health crisis and continue implementing services for individuals to find help, hope and recovery. Visit https://www.behavioralhealth.nd.gov/prevention/suicide to learn more.

post_text:
Did you know that supporting our school is FREE and is as easy as tapping a button? Choose ‚ÄúHONKER NATION PTO‚Äù on AmazonSmile and Amazon will donate to our PTO! AmazonSmile is even available on the Amazon app now, making AmazonSmile easier to access than ever.

While we STRONGLY encourage everyone to shop locally as much as possible, AmazonSmile is an easy way for family and friends all across the country to support our school. Spread the word and help us help make our school the best it can be!

How to set up AmazonSmile on the Amazon app:
1. Menu ‚Äî> Programs & Features ‚Äî> AmazonSmile
2. Choose Charity: Honker Nation PTO (or type in 58746 to choose it from the list)
3. Toggle to ON & follow onscreen prompts

Ordering on Amazon from your computer? Always be sure to go to smile.amazon.com :)

If you have any questions, just let us know! Thanks for supporting PTO!

North Dakota Department of Public Instruction is seeking more families to sign-up for the Waterford Upstart early education program. It is entirely free and 100% online. Child must be 4 by August 1, 2020. Explore the link and website for more information.

(PS Waterford Upstart is NOT an online preschool & it is NOT a substitute for preschool :) )
shared_text:
YOUTUBE.COM
Waterford UPSTART: A State Superintendent explains why she supports this early education program

Little Honkers Preschool
February 12 at 1:53 PM ¬∑

Check out the video below and explore their website for more information. Waterford UPSTART is an early education resource available for free to families of young children in North Dakota!

"This is UPSTART‚Äôs second year in North Dakota! Eligible families will have a child with a birthday between September 1, 2015 - September 2, 2016 and will attend kindergarten in the fall of 2021.

FREE to both families and school districts, this program is funded through a grant from the U.S. Department of Education called Education, Research, and Innovation (EIR).
Parent Orientation is tentatively scheduled in North Dakota the week of August 10th ‚Äì 15th.

Waterford UPSTART is not an online preschool. It is a program that engages & prepares children and supports families for Kindergarten and academic success in school."

www.waterfordupstart.org

shared_text:
Kenmare Public School
March 15 at 11:50 AM ¬∑

I want to inform everyone that parent/teacher conferences will continue as planned. However, the Kenmare Board of Education has decided to cancel the community meeting previously scheduled to begin after conferences. Also, the PTO will not be providing childcare during conferences.
For parents: if you feel ill in any way, we ask that you please not attend conferences. For parents who are ill or do not feel comfortable attending, teachers will make themselves available for a telephone conference. If you will not be attending but would like to have a conference with your child's teacher, please contact that teacher. Remember, absentee ballot applications and ballots will be available during parent/teacher conferences. Thank you for your patience and support.
Dr. Godfrey
